185 template <class T>
186 class Local {
187  public:
188  V8_INLINE Local() : val_(nullptr) {}
189  template <class S>
190  V8_INLINE Local(Local<S> that)
191  : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
197  static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
198  }
199 
203  V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
204 
208  V8_INLINE void Clear() { val_ = nullptr; }
209 
210  V8_INLINE T* operator->() const { return val_; }
211 
212  V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return val_; }
213 
224  template <class S>
225  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Local<S>& that) const {
226  internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_);
227  internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
228  if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
229  if (b == nullptr) return false;
230  return *a == *b;
231  }
232 
233  template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator==(
234  const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
235  internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_);
236  internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
237  if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
238  if (b == nullptr) return false;
239  return *a == *b;
240  }
241 
252  template <class S>
253  V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Local<S>& that) const {
254  return !operator==(that);
255  }
256 
257  template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator!=(
258  const Persistent<S>& that) const {
259  return !operator==(that);
260  }
261 
267  template <class S> V8_INLINE static Local<T> Cast(Local<S> that) {
268 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
269  // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
270  // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
271  if (that.IsEmpty()) return Local<T>();
272 #endif
273  return Local<T>(T::Cast(*that));
274  }
275 
281  template <class S>
282  V8_INLINE Local<S> As() const {
283  return Local<S>::Cast(*this);
284  }
285 
291  V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, Local<T> that);
292  V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate,
293  const PersistentBase<T>& that);
294  V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate,
295  const TracedReferenceBase<T>& that);
296 
297  private:
298  friend class Utils;
299  template<class F> friend class Eternal;
300  template<class F> friend class PersistentBase;
301  template<class F, class M> friend class Persistent;
302  template<class F> friend class Local;
303  template <class F>
304  friend class MaybeLocal;
305  template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
306  template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
307  friend class String;
308  friend class Object;
309  friend class Context;
310  friend class Isolate;
311  friend class Private;
312  template<class F> friend class internal::CustomArguments;
313  friend Local<Primitive> Undefined(Isolate* isolate);
314  friend Local<Primitive> Null(Isolate* isolate);
315  friend Local<Boolean> True(Isolate* isolate);
316  friend Local<Boolean> False(Isolate* isolate);
317  friend class HandleScope;
318  friend class EscapableHandleScope;
319  template <class F1, class F2, class F3>
320  friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
321  template<class F1, class F2> friend class PersistentValueVector;
322  template <class F>
323  friend class ReturnValue;
324  template <class F>
325  friend class Traced;
326  template <class F>
327  friend class TracedGlobal;
328  template <class F>
329  friend class TracedReferenceBase;
330  template <class F>
331  friend class TracedReference;
332 
333  explicit V8_INLINE Local(T* that) : val_(that) {}
334  V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, T* that);
335  T* val_;
336 };

367 
372  template <class S>

374  out->val_ = IsEmpty() ? nullptr : this->val_;

418 static const int kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
419 static const int kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
420 
421 template <typename T>
422 class WeakCallbackInfo {
423  public:
424  typedef void (*Callback)(const WeakCallbackInfo<T>& data);
425 
426  WeakCallbackInfo(Isolate* isolate, T* parameter,
427  void* embedder_fields[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback],
428  Callback* callback)
429  : isolate_(isolate), parameter_(parameter), callback_(callback) {
430  for (int i = 0; i < kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback; ++i) {
431  embedder_fields_[i] = embedder_fields[i];
432  }
433  }
434 
435  V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const { return isolate_; }
436  V8_INLINE T* GetParameter() const { return parameter_; }
437  V8_INLINE void* GetInternalField(int index) const;
438 
439  // When first called, the embedder MUST Reset() the Global which triggered the
440  // callback. The Global itself is unusable for anything else. No v8 other api
441  // calls may be called in the first callback. Should additional work be
442  // required, the embedder must set a second pass callback, which will be
443  // called after all the initial callbacks are processed.
444  // Calling SetSecondPassCallback on the second pass will immediately crash.
445  void SetSecondPassCallback(Callback callback) const { *callback_ = callback; }
446 
447  private:
448  Isolate* isolate_;
449  T* parameter_;
450  Callback* callback_;
451  void* embedder_fields_[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback];
452 };
453 
454 
455 // kParameter will pass a void* parameter back to the callback, kInternalFields
456 // will pass the first two internal fields back to the callback, kFinalizer
457 // will pass a void* parameter back, but is invoked before the object is
458 // actually collected, so it can be resurrected. In the last case, it is not
459 // possible to request a second pass callback.
460 enum class WeakCallbackType { kParameter, kInternalFields, kFinalizer };
461

615 template<class T>
616 class NonCopyablePersistentTraits {
617  public:
618  typedef Persistent<T, NonCopyablePersistentTraits<T> > NonCopyablePersistent;
619  static const bool kResetInDestructor = false;
620  template<class S, class M>
621  V8_INLINE static void Copy(const Persistent<S, M>& source,
622  NonCopyablePersistent* dest) {
623  static_assert(sizeof(S) < 0,
624  "NonCopyablePersistentTraits::Copy is not instantiable");
625  }
626 };

653 template <class T, class M> class Persistent : public PersistentBase<T> {
654  public:
658  V8_INLINE Persistent() : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {}
664  template <class S>
665  V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
666  : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
667  static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
668  }
674  template <class S, class M2>
675  V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, const Persistent<S, M2>& that)
676  : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
677  static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
678  }
685  V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent& that) : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {
686  Copy(that);
687  }
688  template <class S, class M2>
689  V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
690  Copy(that);
691  }
692  V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent& that) {
693  Copy(that);
694  return *this;
695  }
696  template <class S, class M2>
697  V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) { // NOLINT
698  Copy(that);
699  return *this;
700  }
706  V8_INLINE ~Persistent() {
707  if (M::kResetInDestructor) this->Reset();
708  }
709 
710  // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
711  template <class S>
712  V8_INLINE static Persistent<T>& Cast(const Persistent<S>& that) { // NOLINT
713 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
714  // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
715  // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
716  if (!that.IsEmpty()) T::Cast(*that);
717 #endif
718  return reinterpret_cast<Persistent<T>&>(const_cast<Persistent<S>&>(that));
719  }
720 
721  // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
722  template <class S>
723  V8_INLINE Persistent<S>& As() const { // NOLINT
724  return Persistent<S>::Cast(*this);
725  }
726 
727  private:
728  friend class Isolate;
729  friend class Utils;
730  template<class F> friend class Local;
731  template<class F1, class F2> friend class Persistent;
732  template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
733 
734  explicit V8_INLINE Persistent(T* that) : PersistentBase<T>(that) {}
735  V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
736  template<class S, class M2>
737  V8_INLINE void Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that);
738 };

856  internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(val_);
857  internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
858  if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
859  if (b == nullptr) return false;
860  return *a == *b;

865  internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(val_);
866  internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
867  if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
868  if (b == nullptr) return false;

908  DestructionMode destruction_mode);

1065 
1072  template <class S>
1073  TracedReference(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that) : TracedReferenceBase<T>() {
1074  this->val_ = this->New(isolate, that.val_, &this->val_,
1075  TracedReferenceBase<T>::kWithoutDestructor);
1076  static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
1077  }
1078 
1083  V8_INLINE TracedReference(TracedReference&& other) {
1084  // Forward to operator=.
1085  *this = std::move(other);
1086  }
1087 
1092  template <typename S>
1093  V8_INLINE TracedReference(TracedReference<S>&& other) {
1094  // Forward to operator=.
1095  *this = std::move(other);
1096  }
1097 
1102  V8_INLINE TracedReference(const TracedReference& other) {
1103  // Forward to operator=;
1104  *this = other;
1105  }
1106 
1111  template <typename S>
1112  V8_INLINE TracedReference(const TracedReference<S>& other) {
1113  // Forward to operator=;
1114  *this = other;
1115  }
1116 
1120  V8_INLINE TracedReference& operator=(TracedReference&& rhs);
1121 
1125  template <class S>
1126  V8_INLINE TracedReference& operator=(TracedReference<S>&& rhs);
1127 
1131  V8_INLINE TracedReference& operator=(const TracedReference& rhs);
1132 
1136  template <class S>
1137  V8_INLINE TracedReference& operator=(const TracedReference<S>& rhs);
1138 
1143  template <class S>
1144  V8_INLINE void Reset(Isolate* isolate, const Local<S>& other);
1145 
1146  template <class S>
1147  V8_INLINE TracedReference<S>& As() const {
1148  return reinterpret_cast<TracedReference<S>&>(
1149  const_cast<TracedReference<T>&>(*this));
1150  }
1151 };

1332 class ScriptOriginOptions {
1333  public:
1334  V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(bool is_shared_cross_origin = false,
1335  bool is_opaque = false, bool is_wasm = false,
1336  bool is_module = false)
1337  : flags_((is_shared_cross_origin ? kIsSharedCrossOrigin : 0) |
1338  (is_wasm ? kIsWasm : 0) | (is_opaque ? kIsOpaque : 0) |
1339  (is_module ? kIsModule : 0)) {}
1340  V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(int flags)
1341  : flags_(flags &
1342  (kIsSharedCrossOrigin | kIsOpaque | kIsWasm | kIsModule)) {}
1343 
1344  bool IsSharedCrossOrigin() const {
1345  return (flags_ & kIsSharedCrossOrigin) != 0;
1346  }
1347  bool IsOpaque() const { return (flags_ & kIsOpaque) != 0; }
1348  bool IsWasm() const { return (flags_ & kIsWasm) != 0; }
1349  bool IsModule() const { return (flags_ & kIsModule) != 0; }
1350 
1351  int Flags() const { return flags_; }
1352 
1353  private:
1354  enum {
1355  kIsSharedCrossOrigin = 1,
1356  kIsOpaque = 1 << 1,
1357  kIsWasm = 1 << 2,
1358  kIsModule = 1 << 3
1359  };
1360  const int flags_;
1361 };

1614 class V8_EXPORT ScriptCompiler {
1615  public:
1623  struct V8_EXPORT CachedData {
1624  enum BufferPolicy {
1625  BufferNotOwned,
1626  BufferOwned
1627  };
1628 
1629  CachedData()
1630  : data(nullptr),
1631  length(0),
1632  rejected(false),
1633  buffer_policy(BufferNotOwned) {}
1634 
1635  // If buffer_policy is BufferNotOwned, the caller keeps the ownership of
1636  // data and guarantees that it stays alive until the CachedData object is
1637  // destroyed. If the policy is BufferOwned, the given data will be deleted
1638  // (with delete[]) when the CachedData object is destroyed.
1639  CachedData(const uint8_t* data, int length,
1640  BufferPolicy buffer_policy = BufferNotOwned);
1641  ~CachedData();
1642  // TODO(marja): Async compilation; add constructors which take a callback
1643  // which will be called when V8 no longer needs the data.
1644  const uint8_t* data;
1645  int length;
1646  bool rejected;
1647  BufferPolicy buffer_policy;
1648 
1649  // Prevent copying.
1650  CachedData(const CachedData&) = delete;
1651  CachedData& operator=(const CachedData&) = delete;
1652  };

3670  // Implements CreateDataProperty (ECMA-262, 7.3.4).
3671  //
3672  // Defines a configurable, writable, enumerable property with the given value

3693 
3694  // Implements Object.DefineProperty(O, P, Attributes), see Ecma-262 19.1.2.4.
3695  //
3696  // The defineProperty function is used to add an own property or
3697  // update the attributes of an existing own property of an object.
3698  //
3699  // Both data and accessor descriptors can be used.
3700  //
3701  // In general, CreateDataProperty is faster, however, does not allow
3702  // for specifying attributes or an accessor descriptor.
3703  //
3704  // The PropertyDescriptor can change when redefining a property.
3705  //
3706  // Returns true on success.
3707  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT Maybe<bool> DefineProperty(
3708  Local<Context> context, Local<Name> key,
3709  PropertyDescriptor& descriptor); // NOLINT(runtime/references)
3710

3712  Local<Value> key);

4205 template<typename T>
4206 class ReturnValue {
4207  public:
4208  template <class S> V8_INLINE ReturnValue(const ReturnValue<S>& that)
4209  : value_(that.value_) {
4210  static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
4211  }
4212  // Local setters
4213  template <typename S>
4214  V8_INLINE void Set(const Global<S>& handle);
4215  template <typename S>
4216  V8_INLINE void Set(const TracedReferenceBase<S>& handle);
4217  template <typename S>
4218  V8_INLINE void Set(const Local<S> handle);
4219  // Fast primitive setters
4220  V8_INLINE void Set(bool value);
4221  V8_INLINE void Set(double i);
4222  V8_INLINE void Set(int32_t i);
4223  V8_INLINE void Set(uint32_t i);
4224  // Fast JS primitive setters
4225  V8_INLINE void SetNull();
4226  V8_INLINE void SetUndefined();
4227  V8_INLINE void SetEmptyString();
4228  // Convenience getter for Isolate
4229  V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const;
4230 
4231  // Pointer setter: Uncompilable to prevent inadvertent misuse.
4232  template <typename S>
4233  V8_INLINE void Set(S* whatever);
4234 
4235  // Getter. Creates a new Local<> so it comes with a certain performance
4236  // hit. If the ReturnValue was not yet set, this will return the undefined
4237  // value.
4238  V8_INLINE Local<Value> Get() const;
4239 
4240  private:
4241  template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
4242  template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
4243  template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
4244  template <class F, class G, class H>
4245  friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
4246  V8_INLINE void SetInternal(internal::Address value) { *value_ = value; }
4247  V8_INLINE internal::Address GetDefaultValue();
4248  V8_INLINE explicit ReturnValue(internal::Address* slot);
4249  internal::Address* value_;
4250 };

6975 class V8_EXPORT Extension { // NOLINT

6978  // as the Extension itself.

6980  const char** deps = nullptr, int source_length = -1);
6981  virtual ~Extension() { delete source_; }

6983  Isolate* isolate, Local<String> name) {
6984  return Local<FunctionTemplate>();
6985  }
6986 
6987  const char* name() const { return name_; }
6988  size_t source_length() const { return source_length_; }
6989  const String::ExternalOneByteStringResource* source() const {
6990  return source_;
6991  }
6992  int dependency_count() const { return dep_count_; }
6993  const char** dependencies() const { return deps_; }
6994  void set_auto_enable(bool value) { auto_enable_ = value; }
6995  bool auto_enable() { return auto_enable_; }
6996 
6997  // Disallow copying and assigning.
6998  Extension(const Extension&) = delete;
6999  void operator=(const Extension&) = delete;
7000 
7001  private:
7002  const char* name_;
7003  size_t source_length_; // expected to initialize before source_
7004  String::ExternalOneByteStringResource* source_;
7005  int dep_count_;
7006  const char** deps_;
7007  bool auto_enable_;
7008 };

7709 
7715 struct JitCodeEvent {
7716  enum EventType {
7717  CODE_ADDED,
7718  CODE_MOVED,
7719  CODE_REMOVED,
7720  CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO,
7721  CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING,
7722  CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING
7723  };
7724  // Definition of the code position type. The "POSITION" type means the place
7725  // in the source code which are of interest when making stack traces to
7726  // pin-point the source location of a stack frame as close as possible.
7727  // The "STATEMENT_POSITION" means the place at the beginning of each
7728  // statement, and is used to indicate possible break locations.
7729  enum PositionType { POSITION, STATEMENT_POSITION };
7730 
7731  // There are two different kinds of JitCodeEvents, one for JIT code generated
7732  // by the optimizing compiler, and one for byte code generated for the
7733  // interpreter. For JIT_CODE events, the |code_start| member of the event
7734  // points to the beginning of jitted assembly code, while for BYTE_CODE
7735  // events, |code_start| points to the first bytecode of the interpreted
7736  // function.
7737  enum CodeType { BYTE_CODE, JIT_CODE };
7738 
7739  // Type of event.
7740  EventType type;
7741  CodeType code_type;
7742  // Start of the instructions.
7743  void* code_start;
7744  // Size of the instructions.
7745  size_t code_len;
7746  // Script info for CODE_ADDED event.
7747  Local<UnboundScript> script;
7748  // User-defined data for *_LINE_INFO_* event. It's used to hold the source
7749  // code line information which is returned from the
7750  // CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING event. And it's passed to subsequent
7751  // CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO and CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING events.
7752  void* user_data;
7753 
7754  struct name_t {
7755  // Name of the object associated with the code, note that the string is not
7756  // zero-terminated.
7757  const char* str;
7758  // Number of chars in str.
7759  size_t len;
7760  };
7761 
7762  struct line_info_t {
7763  // PC offset
7764  size_t offset;
7765  // Code position
7766  size_t pos;
7767  // The position type.
7768  PositionType position_type;
7769  };
7770 
7771  struct wasm_source_info_t {
7772  // Source file name.
7773  const char* filename;
7774  // Length of filename.
7775  size_t filename_size;
7776  // Line number table, which maps offsets of JITted code to line numbers of
7777  // source file.
7778  const line_info_t* line_number_table;
7779  // Number of entries in the line number table.
7780  size_t line_number_table_size;
7781  };
7782 
7783  wasm_source_info_t* wasm_source_info;
7784 
7785  union {
7786  // Only valid for CODE_ADDED.
7787  struct name_t name;
7788 
7789  // Only valid for CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO
7790  struct line_info_t line_info;
7791 
7792  // New location of instructions. Only valid for CODE_MOVED.
7793  void* new_code_start;
7794  };
7795 
7796  Isolate* isolate;
7797 };
7798 
7804 enum RAILMode : unsigned {
7805  // Response performance mode: In this mode very low virtual machine latency
7806  // is provided. V8 will try to avoid JavaScript execution interruptions.
7807  // Throughput may be throttled.
7808  PERFORMANCE_RESPONSE,
7809  // Animation performance mode: In this mode low virtual machine latency is
7810  // provided. V8 will try to avoid as many JavaScript execution interruptions
7811  // as possible. Throughput may be throttled. This is the default mode.
7812  PERFORMANCE_ANIMATION,
7813  // Idle performance mode: The embedder is idle. V8 can complete deferred work
7814  // in this mode.
7815  PERFORMANCE_IDLE,
7816  // Load performance mode: In this mode high throughput is provided. V8 may
7817  // turn off latency optimizations.
7818  PERFORMANCE_LOAD
7819 };
7820

9893 
9904 template <class T>
9905 class Maybe {
9906  public:
9907  V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !has_value_; }
9908  V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return has_value_; }
9909 
9913  V8_INLINE T ToChecked() const { return FromJust(); }
9914 
9919  V8_INLINE void Check() const {
9920  if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
9921  }
9922 
9927  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool To(T* out) const {
9928  if (V8_LIKELY(IsJust())) *out = value_;
9929  return IsJust();
9930  }
9931 
9936  V8_INLINE T FromJust() const {
9937  if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
9938  return value_;
9939  }
9940 
9945  V8_INLINE T FromMaybe(const T& default_value) const {
9946  return has_value_ ? value_ : default_value;
9947  }
9948 
9949  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
9950  return (IsJust() == other.IsJust()) &&
9951  (!IsJust() || FromJust() == other.FromJust());
9952  }
9953 
9954  V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
9955  return !operator==(other);
9956  }
9957 
9958  private:
9959  Maybe() : has_value_(false) {}
9960  explicit Maybe(const T& t) : has_value_(true), value_(t) {}
9961 
9962  bool has_value_;
9963  T value_;
9964 
9965  template <class U>
9966  friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
9967  template <class U>
9968  friend Maybe<U> Just(const U& u);
9969 };
9970 
9971 template <class T>
9972 inline Maybe<T> Nothing() {
9973  return Maybe<T>();
9974 }
9975 
9976 template <class T>
9977 inline Maybe<T> Just(const T& t) {
9978  return Maybe<T>(t);
9979 }
9980 
9981 // A template specialization of Maybe<T> for the case of T = void.
9982 template <>
9983 class Maybe<void> {
9984  public:
9985  V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !is_valid_; }
9986  V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return is_valid_; }
9987 
9988  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
9989  return IsJust() == other.IsJust();
9990  }
9991 
9992  V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
9993  return !operator==(other);
9994  }
9995 
9996  private:
9997  struct JustTag {};
9998 
9999  Maybe() : is_valid_(false) {}
10000  explicit Maybe(JustTag) : is_valid_(true) {}
10001 
10002  bool is_valid_;
10003 
10004  template <class U>
10005  friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
10006  friend Maybe<void> JustVoid();
10007 };
10008 
10009 inline Maybe<void> JustVoid() { return Maybe<void>(Maybe<void>::JustTag()); }
10010

10021  explicit TryCatch(Isolate* isolate);

10027

10701 template <class T>
10702 Local<T> Local<T>::New(Isolate* isolate, T* that) {
10703  if (that == nullptr) return Local<T>();
10704  T* that_ptr = that;
10705  internal::Address* p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that_ptr);
10706  return Local<T>(reinterpret_cast<T*>(HandleScope::CreateHandle(
10707  reinterpret_cast<internal::Isolate*>(isolate), *p)));
10708 }

10755 template <class T, class M>
10756 template <class S, class M2>
10757 void Persistent<T, M>::Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) {
10758  static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
10759  this->Reset();
10760  if (that.IsEmpty()) return;
10761  internal::Address* p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
10762  this->val_ = reinterpret_cast<T*>(V8::CopyGlobalReference(p));
10763  M::Copy(that, this);
10764 }

10771  I::kNodeStateIsWeakValue;
10772 }

10851 template <class T>

10854  V8::MoveGlobalReference(reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&other.val_),
10855  reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&this->val_));

10857  }

10860 template <class T>
10861 template <class S>
10862 Global<T>& Global<T>::operator=(Global<S>&& rhs) {
10863  static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
10864  if (this != &rhs) {
10865  this->Reset();
10866  if (rhs.val_ != nullptr) {
10867  this->val_ = rhs.val_;
10868  V8::MoveGlobalReference(
10869  reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&rhs.val_),
10870  reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&this->val_));
10871  rhs.val_ = nullptr;
10872  }
10873  }
10874  return *this;
10875 }

10881  internal::Address* p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that);
10882  return reinterpret_cast<T*>(V8::GlobalizeTracedReference(
10883  reinterpret_cast<internal::Isolate*>(isolate), p,
10884  reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(slot),
10885  destruction_mode == kWithDestructor));
10886 }

11062 template<typename T>
11063 void ReturnValue<T>::Set(int32_t i) {
11064  static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, Integer>::value, "type check");
11065  typedef internal::Internals I;
11066  if (V8_LIKELY(I::IsValidSmi(i))) {
11067  *value_ = I::IntToSmi(i);
11068  return;
11069  }
11070  Set(Integer::New(GetIsolate(), i));
11071 }
11072 
11073 template<typename T>
11074 void ReturnValue<T>::Set(uint32_t i) {
11075  static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, Integer>::value, "type check");
11076  // Can't simply use INT32_MAX here for whatever reason.
11077  bool fits_into_int32_t = (i & (1U << 31)) == 0;
11078  if (V8_LIKELY(fits_into_int32_t)) {
11079  Set(static_cast<int32_t>(i));
11080  return;
11081  }
11082  Set(Integer::NewFromUnsigned(GetIsolate(), i));
11083 }
11084 
11085 template<typename T>
11086 void ReturnValue<T>::Set(bool value) {
11087  static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, Boolean>::value, "type check");
11088  typedef internal::Internals I;
11089  int root_index;
11090  if (value) {
11091  root_index = I::kTrueValueRootIndex;
11092  } else {
11093  root_index = I::kFalseValueRootIndex;
11094  }
11095  *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), root_index);
11096 }
11097 
11098 template<typename T>
11099 void ReturnValue<T>::SetNull() {
11100  static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, Primitive>::value, "type check");
11101  typedef internal::Internals I;
11102  *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kNullValueRootIndex);
11103 }
11104 
11105 template<typename T>
11106 void ReturnValue<T>::SetUndefined() {
11107  static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, Primitive>::value, "type check");
11108  typedef internal::Internals I;
11109  *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kUndefinedValueRootIndex);
11110 }
11111 
11112 template<typename T>
11113 void ReturnValue<T>::SetEmptyString() {
11114  static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, String>::value, "type check");
11115  typedef internal::Internals I;
11116  *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kEmptyStringRootIndex);
11117 }
11118 
11119 template <typename T>
11120 Isolate* ReturnValue<T>::GetIsolate() const {
11121  // Isolate is always the pointer below the default value on the stack.
11122  return *reinterpret_cast<Isolate**>(&value_[-2]);
11123 }
11124 
11125 template <typename T>
11126 Local<Value> ReturnValue<T>::Get() const {
11127  typedef internal::Internals I;
11128  if (*value_ == *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kTheHoleValueRootIndex))
11129  return Local<Value>(*Undefined(GetIsolate()));
11130  return Local<Value>::New(GetIsolate(), reinterpret_cast<Value*>(value_));
11131 }
11132 
11133 template <typename T>
11134 template <typename S>
11135 void ReturnValue<T>::Set(S* whatever) {
11136  static_assert(sizeof(S) < 0, "incompilable to prevent inadvertent misuse");
11137 }
11138 
11139 template <typename T>
11140 internal::Address ReturnValue<T>::GetDefaultValue() {
11141  // Default value is always the pointer below value_ on the stack.
11142  return value_[-1];
11143 }

11145 template <typename T>
11146 FunctionCallbackInfo<T>::FunctionCallbackInfo(internal::Address* implicit_args,
11147  internal::Address* values,
11148  int length)
11149  : implicit_args_(implicit_args), values_(values), length_(length) {}
11150 
11151 template<typename T>
11152 Local<Value> FunctionCallbackInfo<T>::operator[](int i) const {
11153  // values_ points to the first argument (not the receiver).
11154  if (i < 0 || length_ <= i) return Local<Value>(*Undefined(GetIsolate()));
11155 #ifdef V8_REVERSE_JSARGS
11156  return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(values_ + i));
11157 #else
11158  return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(values_ - i));
11159 #endif
11160 }

11164 Local<Object> FunctionCallbackInfo<T>::This() const {
11165  // values_ points to the first argument (not the receiver).
11166 #ifdef V8_REVERSE_JSARGS
11167  return Local<Object>(reinterpret_cast<Object*>(values_ - 1));
11168 #else
11169  return Local<Object>(reinterpret_cast<Object*>(values_ + 1));
11170 #endif
11171 }

11324 
11325 Local<Value> Object::GetInternalField(int index) {
11326 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11327  typedef internal::Address A;
11328  typedef internal::Internals I;
11329  A obj = *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this);
11330  // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
11331  // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
11332  auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
11333  if (instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
11334  instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType ||
11335  instance_type == I::kJSSpecialApiObjectType) {
11336  int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
11337  A value = I::ReadRawField<A>(obj, offset);
11338 #ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
11339  // We read the full pointer value and then decompress it in order to avoid
11340  // dealing with potential endiannes issues.
11341  value = I::DecompressTaggedAnyField(obj, static_cast<uint32_t>(value));
11342 #endif
11343  internal::Isolate* isolate =
11344  internal::IsolateFromNeverReadOnlySpaceObject(obj);
11345  A* result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(isolate, value);
11346  return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
11347  }
11348 #endif
11349  return SlowGetInternalField(index);
11350 }
11351 
11352 
11353 void* Object::GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(int index) {
11354 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11355  typedef internal::Address A;
11356  typedef internal::Internals I;
11357  A obj = *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this);
11358  // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
11359  // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
11360  auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
11361  if (V8_LIKELY(instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
11362  instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType ||
11363  instance_type == I::kJSSpecialApiObjectType)) {
11364  int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
11365  return I::ReadRawField<void*>(obj, offset);
11366  }
11367 #endif
11368  return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(index);
11369 }

11379 Local<String> String::Empty(Isolate* isolate) {
11380  typedef internal::Address S;
11381  typedef internal::Internals I;

11384  return Local<String>(reinterpret_cast<String*>(slot));
11385 }

11387 
11388 String::ExternalStringResource* String::GetExternalStringResource() const {
11389  typedef internal::Address A;
11390  typedef internal::Internals I;
11391  A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11392 
11393  ExternalStringResource* result;
11394  if (I::IsExternalTwoByteString(I::GetInstanceType(obj))) {
11395  void* value = I::ReadRawField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
11396  result = reinterpret_cast<String::ExternalStringResource*>(value);
11397  } else {
11398  result = GetExternalStringResourceSlow();
11399  }
11400 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11401  VerifyExternalStringResource(result);
11402 #endif
11403  return result;
11404 }
11405 
11406 
11407 String::ExternalStringResourceBase* String::GetExternalStringResourceBase(
11408  String::Encoding* encoding_out) const {
11409  typedef internal::Address A;
11410  typedef internal::Internals I;
11411  A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11412  int type = I::GetInstanceType(obj) & I::kFullStringRepresentationMask;
11413  *encoding_out = static_cast<Encoding>(type & I::kStringEncodingMask);
11414  ExternalStringResourceBase* resource;
11415  if (type == I::kExternalOneByteRepresentationTag ||
11416  type == I::kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag) {
11417  void* value = I::ReadRawField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
11418  resource = static_cast<ExternalStringResourceBase*>(value);
11419  } else {
11420  resource = GetExternalStringResourceBaseSlow(encoding_out);
11421  }
11422 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11423  VerifyExternalStringResourceBase(resource, *encoding_out);
11424 #endif
11425  return resource;
11426 }

11437 bool Value::QuickIsUndefined() const {
11438  typedef internal::Address A;
11439  typedef internal::Internals I;
11440  A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11441  if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
11442  if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
11443  return (I::GetOddballKind(obj) == I::kUndefinedOddballKind);
11444 }

11455 bool Value::QuickIsNull() const {

11457  typedef internal::Internals I;
11458  A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11459  if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
11460  if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
11461  return (I::GetOddballKind(obj) == I::kNullOddballKind);
11462 }

11467 #else

11469 #endif
11470 }
11471 
11472 bool Value::QuickIsNullOrUndefined() const {
11473  typedef internal::Address A;
11474  typedef internal::Internals I;
11475  A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11476  if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
11477  if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
11478  int kind = I::GetOddballKind(obj);
11479  return kind == I::kNullOddballKind || kind == I::kUndefinedOddballKind;
11480 }

11930 
11931 int64_t Isolate::AdjustAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemory(
11932  int64_t change_in_bytes) {
11933  typedef internal::Internals I;
11934  constexpr int64_t kMemoryReducerActivationLimit = 32 * 1024 * 1024;
11935  int64_t* external_memory = reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
11936  reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) + I::kExternalMemoryOffset);
11937  int64_t* external_memory_limit = reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
11938  reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) + I::kExternalMemoryLimitOffset);
11939  int64_t* external_memory_low_since_mc =
11940  reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) +
11941  I::kExternalMemoryLowSinceMarkCompactOffset);
11942 
11943  // Embedders are weird: we see both over- and underflows here. Perform the
11944  // addition with unsigned types to avoid undefined behavior.
11945  const int64_t amount =
11946  static_cast<int64_t>(static_cast<uint64_t>(change_in_bytes) +
11947  static_cast<uint64_t>(*external_memory));
11948  *external_memory = amount;
11949 
11950  if (amount < *external_memory_low_since_mc) {
11951  *external_memory_low_since_mc = amount;
11952  *external_memory_limit = amount + I::kExternalAllocationSoftLimit;
11953  }
11954 
11955  if (change_in_bytes <= 0) return *external_memory;
11956 
11957  int64_t allocation_diff_since_last_mc = static_cast<int64_t>(
11958  static_cast<uint64_t>(*external_memory) -
11959  static_cast<uint64_t>(*external_memory_low_since_mc));
11960  // Only check memory pressure and potentially trigger GC if the amount of
11961  // external memory increased.
11962  if (allocation_diff_since_last_mc > kMemoryReducerActivationLimit) {
11963  CheckMemoryPressure();
11964  }
11965  if (amount > *external_memory_limit) {
11966  ReportExternalAllocationLimitReached();
11967  }
11968  return *external_memory;
11969 }
11970 
11971 Local<Value> Context::GetEmbedderData(int index) {
11972 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11973  typedef internal::Address A;
11974  typedef internal::Internals I;
11975  A ctx = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11976  A embedder_data =
11977  I::ReadTaggedPointerField(ctx, I::kNativeContextEmbedderDataOffset);
11978  int value_offset =
11979  I::kEmbedderDataArrayHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
11980  A value = I::ReadRawField<A>(embedder_data, value_offset);
11981 #ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
11982  // We read the full pointer value and then decompress it in order to avoid
11983  // dealing with potential endiannes issues.
11984  value =
11985  I::DecompressTaggedAnyField(embedder_data, static_cast<uint32_t>(value));
11986 #endif
11987  internal::Isolate* isolate = internal::IsolateFromNeverReadOnlySpaceObject(
11988  *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this));
11989  A* result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(isolate, value);
11990  return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
11991 #else
11992  return SlowGetEmbedderData(index);
11993 #endif
11994 }
11995 
11996 
11997 void* Context::GetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderData(int index) {
11998 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11999  typedef internal::Address A;
12000  typedef internal::Internals I;
12001  A ctx = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
12002  A embedder_data =
12003  I::ReadTaggedPointerField(ctx, I::kNativeContextEmbedderDataOffset);
12004  int value_offset =
12005  I::kEmbedderDataArrayHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
12006  return I::ReadRawField<void*>(embedder_data, value_offset);
12007 #else
12008  return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderData(index);
12009 #endif
12010 }
